title: Driver Arrested In High-Speed Pursuit With Baby On Board
text:
LANCASTER (CBSLA.com) — Sheriff’s deputies chased a driver they say was wanted in a robbery Tuesday while a baby was in the car.
The chase started in Palmdale around 6:15 p.m. and ended around 6:45 p.m. in Lancaster near Cemetery Road when the driver attempted to crash through a gate. Deputies arrested a male and female and then took the toddler into protective custody.

Stay with CBSLA.com and KCAL9 for more details.
